	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_IMPROVEMENT_3EKI">
			<Text>Eki</Text>
			<Gender>neuter:a</Gender>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CIV5_IMPROVEMENTS_3EKI_TEXT">
			<Text>Nomadic pastoralism is a form of pastoralism where livestock are herded in order to find fresh pastures on which to graze. Strictly speaking, true nomads (like the Huns) follow an irregular pattern of movement, in contrast with transhumance where seasonal pastures are fixed. However this distinction is often not observed and the term nomad used for both—in historical cases the regularity of movements is often unknown in any case. Nomadic pastoralism is commonly practised in regions with little arable land, typically in the developing world. Of the estimated 30 to 40 million nomadic pastoralists worldwide, most are found in central Asia and the Sahel region of West Africa. Increasing numbers of stock may lead to overgrazing of the area and desertification if lands are not allowed to fully recover between one grazing period and the next.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]An Eki can only be built on flat Grassland or Plains tiles. It provides [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production and [ICON_FOOD] Food, and extra [ICON_FOOD] Food if Fertilizer/Civil Service is researched. Removes any features on the tile.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CIV5_IMPROVEMENTS_3EKI_HELP">
			<Text>An Eki can only be built on flat Grassland or Plains tiles. It provides [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production and [ICON_FOOD] Food. It provides more [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production with Chivalry and more [ICON_FOOD] Food after researching Fertilizer (or Civil Service, if the tile is located next to a source of Fresh Water). Removes any features on the tile.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILD_3EKI">
			<Text>Construct an [LINK=IMPROVEMENT_EKI]Eki[\LINK]</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILD_3EKI_HELP">
			<Text>Constructs an Eki, which increases the [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production and [ICON_FOOD] Food of a tile. Must be build on flat Plains or Grasslands. </Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILD_3EKI_REC">
			<Text>It will increase the [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production and [ICON_FOOD] Food on this tile.</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
